	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="UK15PG_DIGESTDOC_issue">
		<title>
			<sourcexml>issue</sourcexml>
			<lnpid>id-UK15-30448</lnpid>
		</title>
		<body>
			<p><sourcexml>issue</sourcexml> becomes
					<targetxml>seclaw:levelinfo/miscdate[@datetype="form-date"]/date-text</targetxml>.
				The attribute <sourcexml>issue/@num</sourcexml> is dropped if present. The
					<targetxml>miscdate/@datetype</targetxml> attribute is always set to
				"form-date".</p>
			<note><targetxml>seclaw:levelinfo</targetxml> is a child of the
					<targetxml>seclaw:level</targetxml> created from
				<sourcexml>dig:info</sourcexml>.</note>
			<note>This scenario occurs in smart forms, dpsi 0JUM and 0KVS. This is alternative
				mark-up to the <sourcexml>dig:info/otherinfo</sourcexml> element (see the topic
					<xref href="UK15PG_DIGESTDOC_otherinfo.dita"/>). Either one or the other of
				these elements will be present in a document, both are mapped to
					<targetxml>miscdate[@datetype="form-date"]</targetxml>.</note>

			<example>
				<title>Source XML</title>
				<codeblock> &lt;dig:body&gt; &lt;dig:info&gt; &lt;issue num="SI 2010/1941"&gt;SI
					2010/1941&lt;/issue&gt; &lt;/dig:info&gt; &lt;/dig:body&gt; </codeblock>
				<title>Target XML</title>
				<codeblock> &lt;seclaw:body&gt; &lt;seclaw:level leveltype="form"&gt;
					&lt;seclaw:levelinfo&gt; &lt;miscdate
					datetype="form-date"&gt;&lt;date-text&gt;2nd Edition Oct
					2004&lt;/date-text&gt;&lt;/miscdate&gt; &lt;/seclaw:levelinfo&gt;
					&lt;/seclaw:level&gt; &lt;/seclaw:body&gt; </codeblock>
			</example>
			<section>
				<title>Changes</title>
